[B] COVID-19 (288) - USA: high vaccine effectiveness against death and hospitalization
More than 99.9% of those fully vaccinated have not had a serious post-vaccination infection, according to the CDC.
Date: Tue 10 Aug 2021
Source: Memesita [abridged, edited]
https://www.memesita.com/more-than-99-9-of-those-vaccinated-have-not-had-a-serious-subsequent-infection/


More than 164 million people in the United States were vaccinated as of 2 Aug [2021], according to the CDC. Less than 0.001% of that total -- 1507 people -- died, and less than 0.005% -- 7101 people -- were hospitalized for COVID-19.

