[In the past 24 hours, 16 countries including the USA (71 135), India (36 127), Brazil (31 142), Iran (29 700), UK (29 143), Indonesia (28 598), France (24 427), Mexico (23 642), Russia (22 144), Thailand (21 882), Malaysia (20 670), Japan (20 490), Turkey (19 949), Philippines (14 019), South Africa (13 020), and Morocco (10 240) have reported the highest numbers of cases, all reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. A global total of 8898 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 12 Aug 2021 to late 13 Aug 2021). A total of 49 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 21 of the 49 countries are from the European region, 7 are from the Americas region, 7 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 5 are from the Western Pacific region, and 4 are from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 6.3%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 1.9%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 26.1% increase in daily reported cases and 25.6% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported over 550 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 207.52 million cumulative reported cases and over 4.36 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
